    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i hear a lot of the local owners saying the \"innovation\" part sounds a bit optimistic. they're mostly worried the upfront costs for the new tech are gonna kill their margins before they ever see those long-term savings. do you have any data or specific arguments on how much the compliance costs usually hit small shops vs the actual benefit they get back?",
