      "content": "These regulations are fundamentally designed to enforce a necessary standard of environmental stewardship, and the initial burden on small businesses is a predictable, albeit difficult, consequence of that mandate. While large corporations can absorb costs more easily, the regulations are not exclusively for them; they are a baseline requirement for all industrial activity. The focus must be on ensuring the government provides robust, accessible support mechanisms, not just the regulations themselves, to make compliance a manageable reality for every shop.",
